parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warped Brake Rotors and Pulsating/Vibrating Steering Wheel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warped brake rotors can cause the steering wheel to vibrate or pulsate, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds. This can lead to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The design flaw in the brake system can cause the brake rotors to warp, leading to vibrating or pulsating steering wheel, difficulty stopping, and loss of control.
The failure of the driver's seat frame can cause the seat to become unstable, move excessively, or even detach from its tracks, increasing the risk of serious injury or accidents.
symptoms: The driver's seat wobbles or rocks from front to back
the seat drops or falls to one side
the seat mounts or brackets break or crack
the seat detaches from its tracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Warning Light and Intermittent Chime
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the airbag light stays on all the time
the chime goes off very often

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy during a collision
the seat belt does not hold.
